The paper deals with a problem related to social networks and influence maximization, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Additionally, the problem involves constraints and optimization, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of submodular utility functions also suggests a possible connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the title explicitly mentions "social networks," which further supports the likelihood of the paper belonging to the cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) sub-category.
